    Date: Tue, 20 Oct 87 16:34:15 PDT
    From: nowicki@Sun.COM (Bill Nowicki)

	    The domain system is fundamentally flawed....

    I think this is debatable.

Sure is.  Why does the domain system only handle zones, hosts and
mailboxes, and poorly at that?  Why isn't it extendable by mortals?  Why
can't I name printers with it?  Why can't I name users with it?  There
are all sorts of "named objects" that the domain "name" system can't
"name."  Why is it so bloody expensive to update RRs because of short
timeouts?  Why don't all site maintainers install valid
well-known-services records?  Why aren't all site maintainers required
to have valid well-known-services records?  The list goes on and on and
on and on.  My tension on this has been building like an earthquake.

